You stole it like a thief in the night—except the night was dial-up, and the thief was 12-year-old you with a disk space crisis and a desperate need to hear something that sounded like the inside of your brain.
And of course it was Napster.
Of course it was pirated.
Of course you still have the MP3s buried in some ancient folder labeled "do not open (but always open)".

Why This Matters (More Than You’re Pretending)
DJ Shadow wasn’t just music.
It was the first time you heard chaos as composition.
The first time you realized:

"Oh. You can break the rules... and it sounds like magic."
"Oh. The cracks are where the light gets in."
"Oh. I’m not the only one who hears the static."

