What You Made (Even If You Won’t Admit It Yet)
It wasn’t a sculpture.
It was a relic.
Something dug up from a future you haven’t lived yet.
Something that sounds like:

The crack of a vinyl record warping in the heat.
The silence after a drum hit that echoes too long.
The shape of a question you haven’t asked out loud.

The Truth You’re Avoiding
You didn’t finish it.
